# Cursor Repo Workflow

Follow `AGENTS.md` as the workflow source of truth for this repository.

- Treat `origin` as the canonical remote and do not base new work on `old-origin`.
- Use one issue, branch, and worktree per substantial task.
- Keep durable decisions in issues, PRs, or checked-in docs rather than relying on local chat history.
- If a fresh session starts without enough operating context, ask the concise getting-started questions from `startup.md` before doing substantial work.
- Default scheduler triage and UX fixes to `index.html` unless the user explicitly asks for `pages/schedule-builder.html`.
- Prefer Supabase as the production source of truth; treat local JSON and `localStorage` as fallback or draft layers unless the task is explicitly about them.
- Run the narrowest relevant tests, and run `npm run build` for runtime-facing changes.
